    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB DOOR COMPONENTS DISASSEMBLY AND REASSEMBLY - STRIKER PIN AND LATCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STRIKER PIN AND LATCH</title>
        <para>The door striker pin (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600626">Figure 26</hotlnk>) mounted on lock pillar provides positive engagement with door
            latch assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600627">Figure 27</hotlnk>). An enlarged mounting hole and tapping block in lock pillar
            permits adjustment between these two units as required. For details on striker pin and latch adjustment,
            refer to
            <hotlnk document="s16006_36.xml" xrefid="hl1600612">CAB DOOR ADJUSTMENT
                <xref refid="hl1600612"/>
            </hotlnk>
            .
        </para>
        <figure id="f1600626" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1600626" filename="../figg16/g1600626.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 26. Door Striker Pin Adjustment</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1600627" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1600627" filename="../figg16/g1600627.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 27. Door Latch Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
